        <li>Self-employed people and sole proprietors who pay themselves from business income</li>
        <li>Small business owners who need to generate pay stubs for their employees</li>
        <li>W-2 employees who have lost or cannot access their employer-issued stubs</li>
      </ul>

      <p>In all of these cases, the pay stub is documentation of real income. The tool helps format that documentation properly.</p>

      <h2>Acceptable Use: The Legal Line</h2>

      <p>There is a clear legal line: using a pay stub that accurately documents real income you actually earned is legal. Using a pay stub that misrepresents income you did not earn — to obtain a loan, rental housing, or any financial product or government benefit — is fraud.</p>

      <p>Specifically, if you use a fraudulent pay stub:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>To obtain a mortgage loan or home equity loan, you may be committing bank fraud under 18 U.S.C. § 1344 (up to 30 years in federal prison, $1 million fine)</li>
        <li>To submit an application electronically, you may be committing wire fraud under 18 U.S.C. § 1343 (up to 20 years per count, or 30 years if affecting a financial institution)</li>
        <li>To submit an application through the mail, you may be committing mail fraud under 18 U.S.C. § 1341 (same penalties as wire fraud)</li>
        <li>You may also face state-level forgery, fraud, and false document charges in addition to federal charges</li>
      </ul>

      <p>These are serious federal felonies with multi-decade prison exposure. "I found a free tool online" is not a defense. The tool generates a document; what you put in that document is your responsibility.</p>

      <p><strong>By using PayStub.fyi, you represent that the information you enter reflects income you actually earned and that you are using the generated pay stub to document real, accurate income — not to misrepresent income to any party.</strong></p>

